Transport officials are manning the country's major routes as holiday travel picks up - ahead of Christmas. Courtesy of #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Transport officials are manning the country's major routes as holiday travel picks up ahead of Christmas. Gauteng Transport MEC, Jacob Mamabolo, says there's a push to ensure vehicles are roadworthy and that drivers comply with COVID-19 safety protocols. READ: OR Tambo airport marks peak day for travel Those who don't will face punishment. Mamabolo said, "operations like these by our law enforcement agencies definitely have a positive impact in terms of two things: one -- making sure that we enforce protocols, laws, and regulations relating to road safety. Secondly, they are definitely impacting the space because we're checking compliance with protocols for COVID-19." - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.